main event: The report describes an observation made on March 18, 1952 in Old Westbury, L.I., N.Y. of an object that appeared like a cloud or round ball moving very fast towards the east.
interesting points: The object was observed for only 5-10 seconds.
The object was traveling very fast and disappeared below the trees and clouds.
The observer was a lady who was flying children.
Other jets were observed in the area at the same time.
The report concludes that this was a mistaken identification of a conventional object due to unusual or adverse weather conditions.
sighted object: A cloud-like or round ball-shaped object
photographs: No photograph present in the report
